Simple Formatting \
\
Simple formatting can be used to add emphasis to words, set headings apart from the rest of the text or just make the printed document more visually appealing.  Bolding, italicizing, and underlining words or phrases sets them apart from the surrounding text and gives them emphasis. Centering a line lets people know that it is some kind of title or heading. \
